WEBVTT

00:00.098 --> 00:10.830
Today, we're wrapping up the series, A Church Every Community Needs, and we've been talking about the fact that the local church is Jesus' movement that represents Him here on earth.

00:10.870 --> 00:15.415
That's why the metaphor is used for the church, that we are the body of Christ, and He is the head.

00:15.455 --> 00:25.185
And so, He started this movement over 2,000 years ago, and you can go anywhere in the world, even in places where Christians are persecuted, and you can find this movement there.

00:25.366 --> 00:26.747
It's unbelievable.

00:26.787 --> 00:29.490
The local church is the hope of the world and the movement

00:29.858 --> 00:30.499
of Jesus.

00:31.160 --> 00:33.865
Now, today I want to start by asking you this question.

00:34.526 --> 00:45.624
If you were going to a brand new city, let's say you were moving today and somebody said to you, you said to somebody, I'm looking for a church and they said, what kind of church are you looking for?

00:45.684 --> 00:47.567
What would be your answer?

00:48.669 --> 00:51.373
Now, some of you might say, well, I'm looking for a Bible believing church.

00:51.433 --> 00:54.418
Okay, well, that's pretty broad for some people.

00:54.562 --> 00:56.224
Well, I'm looking for a church that falls Jesus.

00:56.264 --> 00:57.926
Okay, that's pretty broad for some people.

00:57.946 --> 00:59.487
And then the person said, well, what else?

00:59.568 --> 01:00.969
What else are you looking for?

01:01.009 --> 01:05.354
And you might say, well, I hope they have great music.

01:05.714 --> 01:07.216
Like, I hope the music is good.

01:07.917 --> 01:13.743
Okay, well, they would say, I know a church that has great music, but they don't serve coffee just so you know.

01:15.846 --> 01:19.810
You would say, well, I can only meet Jesus after I caffeinate.

01:19.930 --> 01:23.314
I can't meet him pre-caffeination.

01:23.458 --> 01:27.384
So I definitely need a church with coffee and great music.

01:27.404 --> 01:28.486
Okay, good, good, good.

01:28.546 --> 01:29.647
Well, I know a church like that.

01:29.667 --> 01:31.891
They got coffee, they got music.

01:32.251 --> 01:33.593
It's like 50 people.

01:33.934 --> 01:35.096
You're like, oh, 50 people.

01:35.136 --> 01:36.217
That's too small for me.

01:36.257 --> 01:39.863
I'm looking for like something bigger.

01:39.963 --> 01:41.345
Well, I know another one that has a thousand.

01:41.365 --> 01:42.246
Oh, that's too big.

01:42.407 --> 01:43.128
That's too big.

01:43.508 --> 01:49.377
Like I need it somewhere between 50 and 300 with music and coffee.

01:49.417 --> 01:51.480
And then, well, what about the preaching?

01:51.540 --> 01:52.722
Well, you know, the preachers.

01:55.202 --> 01:59.968
You know, I don't want to say, but he's long.

02:00.749 --> 02:01.450
Ooh, how long?

02:01.470 --> 02:03.953
45 minutes, that's too long.

02:04.213 --> 02:08.959
I need like a 30 to 40 minute window, but there has to be this size and I need to have coffee.

02:09.219 --> 02:13.665
And you know what's interesting to me is how quickly we get caught up in that kind of thing.

02:15.427 --> 02:17.389
And we lose sight of a different question.

02:18.430 --> 02:22.055
And the question is, what is the purpose of the local church?

02:22.856 --> 02:24.658
What is it actually about?

02:25.410 --> 02:34.058
Because you know what, if you call this church or home, we spend a lot of time and a lot of energy and a lot of resources making all of this happen, why?

02:34.098 --> 02:36.200
Like we should know why.

02:36.220 --> 02:41.205
Nobody would run any organization without knowing the purpose of why.

02:41.285 --> 02:42.446
You would never do that.

02:43.407 --> 02:45.849
So what is the purpose of the local church?

02:45.869 --> 02:47.531
But here's the challenge we can have.

02:48.412 --> 02:55.378
Our ideas about the purpose of the church are often skewed by our pursuit

02:55.650 --> 03:00.858
of comfort, the thing that makes us comfortable, the thing that we want.

03:00.918 --> 03:07.708
Without clarity on purpose, the church in our humanity will always choose preference.

03:08.950 --> 03:11.033
We will always choose preference over purpose.

03:11.093 --> 03:12.735
That is part of our humanity.

03:12.815 --> 03:15.019
And you see this all the time.

03:15.780 --> 03:21.148
I had a friend of mine who he said, listen, we have a church, they're looking for a place to meet.

03:21.628 --> 03:25.554
And they said, there's this old church in town, beautiful old building,

03:25.762 --> 03:27.223
There's 20 people in it.

03:27.864 --> 03:33.229
And they, and I asked if we could use their building and I said, you can use it in the afternoon, but under one condition.

03:34.130 --> 03:34.971
And he said, well, what is it?

03:35.011 --> 03:37.073
They said, you cannot move or touch anything.

03:38.334 --> 03:40.256
It all has to stay exactly where it is.

03:41.537 --> 03:42.398
And he said, oh, why?

03:42.478 --> 03:50.966
Well, you know, that's the chair that like Aunt Gertrude donated money and we bought that chair and now she's gone.

03:51.907 --> 03:54.770
But like we want it, we want it there because it reminds us of her.

03:55.618 --> 03:55.858
Right?

03:55.939 --> 04:01.127
And it's like, and these offering plates, this is the offering plate that Jesus used at the last supper.

04:01.207 --> 04:02.249
It's been here that long.

04:03.230 --> 04:04.553
And we don't want that to move.

04:04.873 --> 04:06.937
And we have these memories and we got to preserve it.

04:06.957 --> 04:08.339
And we needed to keep it just the same.

04:08.699 --> 04:10.923
Like to me, I call that museum church.

04:12.506 --> 04:20.018
The preference is to preserve the memories of what God has done in the past and not focus on God wants to do now.

04:20.674 --> 04:22.456
There are all kinds of preferences we have at church.

04:22.496 --> 04:24.297
Some people, you might have a preference.

04:24.317 --> 04:28.121
Some people have a preference for a church that actually tells them they need to hide from the world.

04:28.481 --> 04:29.242
Be afraid.

04:30.483 --> 04:32.625
And you can actually build a huge church that way.

04:32.966 --> 04:35.288
Tell everybody the culture's out to get them.

04:35.788 --> 04:37.530
The culture's trying to persecute them.

04:38.151 --> 04:39.332
And so they need to hide.

04:39.752 --> 04:44.276
So they need to come to the fortress every Sunday and hide out in church.

04:45.217 --> 04:48.440
And so that I can tell you, well, it's a big, bad word out there.

04:48.480 --> 04:50.162
You've got to come here to find Jesus.

04:50.818 --> 04:52.640
It's like a fortress church mentality.

04:52.660 --> 04:53.741
It's a preference.

04:55.283 --> 04:58.907
For some people, their preference is, it's all about music.

04:59.027 --> 05:01.650
I don't actually, I don't really worry about the message.

05:01.971 --> 05:04.634
I just want the worship, the music to be good.

05:04.934 --> 05:07.557
Great music, good vibes.

05:08.098 --> 05:12.202
And they have to at least every Sunday play one of the songs I really like.

05:13.283 --> 05:15.085
Because man, I love it when they play that song.

05:15.126 --> 05:16.847
Like that's my jam when they play that.

05:17.308 --> 05:19.090
So they have to play that at least

05:19.362 --> 05:21.806
Once a month, I have to have songs I know.

05:21.826 --> 05:23.929
It's got to be the worship I like.

05:23.949 --> 05:25.932
It has to be the vibes I want.

05:26.012 --> 05:33.584
And in some ways, you're looking for a church, if that's you, that's more like karaoke night on Friday night than church, right?

05:34.185 --> 05:36.608
The lyrics are on the screen and you get to sing your hits.

05:36.708 --> 05:37.550
That's karaoke.

05:37.990 --> 05:38.631
It's not worship.

05:39.493 --> 05:41.696
And coming and saying, well, that's what I want.

05:41.916 --> 05:43.679
All I want is to come sing and have good vibes.

05:43.959 --> 05:45.001
I don't want any community.

05:45.021 --> 05:46.283
I don't want any accountability.

05:46.303 --> 05:48.306
I don't want anybody to call me on my stuff.

05:48.610 --> 05:52.494
I don't want anything difficult or uncomfortable or challenging.

05:54.176 --> 06:05.688
And for some people, they get to the point where I've tried everything and nobody does youth ministry like me or nobody does services like me or nobody does kids ministry like me.

06:05.708 --> 06:09.532
So what I'm going to do is start my own thing and I will start the church of me.

06:11.154 --> 06:14.898
And then when I start my own thing, then I will have my preferences met.

06:16.898 --> 06:21.724
And what happens is we lose sight of the purpose of the local church.

06:22.685 --> 06:25.229
Why this is Jesus' movement?

06:25.929 --> 06:27.331
Why is it the local church?

06:27.351 --> 06:28.953
And what is the purpose of it?

06:29.714 --> 06:40.848
And we've been looking at this series about if we are the body of Christ, if we are called the body of Christ, His representatives on earth, we've been talking about in this series, but then we need to reflect Christ.

06:40.928 --> 06:42.550
The local church should look like Jesus.

06:42.911 --> 06:45.394
So what was the purpose of Jesus

06:45.506 --> 06:47.449
when he was on this earth.

06:47.529 --> 06:48.431
What was his purpose?

06:49.893 --> 06:58.387
Well, there are a lot of places he talks about it, but the most succinct, if there's one liner, I'm like, man, Jesus took it all and put it in one sentence.

06:58.988 --> 07:01.132
It's after he hangs up with a guy named Zacchaeus.

07:01.172 --> 07:02.534
We've talked about Zacchaeus before.

07:03.195 --> 07:07.182
And Zacchaeus is a tax collector who were like traders in that culture.

07:07.542 --> 07:12.370
He's hanging out with a bunch of other people that religious leaders didn't want Jesus to hang out with.

07:12.642 --> 07:17.508
And Jesus says this at the end of that interaction with those religious leaders.

07:17.528 --> 07:19.211
He says, this is why I'm with these people.

07:19.992 --> 07:25.779
For the son of man, me, came to seek and save those who are lost.

07:27.161 --> 07:31.146
If you want to know why I'm here, I'm here to find people who don't know me.

07:31.707 --> 07:33.870
I'm here to find people who don't know the hope of me.

07:34.310 --> 07:36.573
I'm here to find people who are looking for forgiveness.

07:36.934 --> 07:38.596
I'm here to walk with those who are hurting.

07:38.836 --> 07:40.178
I'm here to walk with those who have

07:40.258 --> 07:46.846
who are struggling with shame and for them surrender their lives to me so that they can be found.

07:47.547 --> 07:49.870
That's my purpose.

07:49.890 --> 07:51.592
So what does this look like for us?

07:51.652 --> 07:54.135
What does it look like for the local church?

07:55.017 --> 07:59.242
Because what we've been talking about is how we need to reflect Jesus.

07:59.482 --> 08:01.685
And we looked at the personality of Jesus.

08:02.726 --> 08:06.771
We looked at that it's not a club for the found, but a search party for the lost.

08:06.811 --> 08:08.914
We looked at the posture of Jesus.

08:09.186 --> 08:12.672
that there's no bottom to humility and no lid on love with Jesus.

08:13.754 --> 08:23.432
And we looked at the power of Jesus last week and the power of the Holy Spirit, but before the Holy Spirit comes, Jesus actually tells the local church his purpose.

08:23.752 --> 08:30.064
He takes his purpose to seek and save the loss and actually passes it off to the local church.

08:31.546 --> 08:33.650
And this all happens

08:34.050 --> 08:35.372
at the end of Matthew.

08:35.392 --> 08:39.538
And I wanna show you the passage where Jesus passes us the baton of purpose.

08:40.239 --> 08:46.909
It says this, then the 11 disciples in Matthew 28, left for Galilee, going to the mountain where Jesus had told them to go.

08:47.350 --> 08:53.058
And when they saw him, they worshiped him, but some of them doubted.

08:53.739 --> 08:57.685
So side note, if you're somebody who sometimes doubts, you're in good company.

08:58.206 --> 09:03.794
These people saw Jesus die, saw him rose again, and still they're like, man, I don't know, this is a lot.

09:06.274 --> 09:07.175
You're in good company.

09:08.176 --> 09:13.242
And he says, Jesus came and told his disciples, I've been given all authority in heaven and earth.

09:13.362 --> 09:13.982
I've died.

09:14.323 --> 09:15.284
I've risen again.

09:15.544 --> 09:16.806
I've done what God has asked.

09:17.406 --> 09:17.927
I've won.

09:17.987 --> 09:26.016
He says, therefore, go and make disciples of all nations.

09:26.036 --> 09:28.498
It could be translated as you are going.

09:28.539 --> 09:31.902
As you are going is more the translation about your life.

09:32.102 --> 09:35.346
As you are going, make apprentices of Jesus, make

09:35.522 --> 09:36.824
followers of Jesus.

09:37.966 --> 09:42.773
Show people how to follow Jesus, baptizing them in the name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

09:43.334 --> 09:52.327
And teach these new disciples to obey all the commands I have given you and be sure of this, I am with you always even to the end of the age.

09:54.010 --> 09:59.938
You see here at the end of Matthew, he's passing the baton and saying the purpose of the church is to make apprentices of Jesus.

09:59.999 --> 10:02.322
The purpose of the church is to show people

10:02.402 --> 10:05.326
who Jesus is, the hope of Jesus, how to follow Jesus.

10:05.646 --> 10:07.209
This is very, very clear here.

10:07.349 --> 10:19.125
And then you go to the book of Acts, this transitions very quickly over to the book of Acts in Acts 1, and he says this, but you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes upon you.

10:19.145 --> 10:31.922
This is the power of Jesus, and you will be my witnesses telling them about me everywhere in Jerusalem, through Judea, in Samaria, and to the ends of the earth, locally, globally, nationally.

10:32.002 --> 10:34.225
He's saying, the Holy Spirit's going to empower you.

10:34.245 --> 10:35.427
We saw that last week.

10:35.447 --> 10:37.911
And now you're going to make apprentices.

10:37.931 --> 10:39.713
You're going to show people how to follow Jesus.

10:39.733 --> 10:41.516
You're going to share that with them.

10:41.556 --> 10:43.479
This is seeking, saving the loss.

10:43.559 --> 10:53.353
The purpose of Jesus, if you want to put it one sentence, the purpose of the church is to share the hope of Jesus with those around us and show people how to follow him.

10:54.495 --> 10:59.282
Purpose of the church, if we want to share the hope of Jesus, those around us and show people how to follow them.

10:59.490 --> 11:02.074
your neighbors, your friends, the people in our community.

11:02.094 --> 11:03.997
That's the type of church our community needs.

11:05.139 --> 11:13.912
Now, if you are a follower of Jesus and you have been for any time, you would probably say, Jeff, I already know this.

11:14.974 --> 11:16.716
Why are we talking about this again?

11:16.736 --> 11:17.738
We've talked about this before.

11:18.118 --> 11:19.280
Why are we talking about this again?

11:19.521 --> 11:28.274
Let me tell you why, because naturally as human beings, we drift towards our insider preferences.

11:30.146 --> 11:35.933
Nobody ever, you never drift towards being about other people, right?

11:36.793 --> 11:41.559
Nobody drifts towards, you know, I just suddenly became a generous person, just drifted into it.

11:42.540 --> 11:46.364
I just, you know, I just suddenly started sacrificing for people.

11:47.425 --> 11:49.548
No, that's an intentional choice.

11:50.269 --> 11:52.751
If we drift, we always drift towards ourselves.

11:53.412 --> 11:54.994
We always drift towards what we want.

11:55.266 --> 11:57.089
We always drift towards what we can have.

11:57.329 --> 12:02.196
And so this is a conversation that we need to continue to have as a local church.

12:03.017 --> 12:13.652
Because at the heart, listen, what Jesus is saying is that the heart of the body of Christ is a commitment to sacrifice so that people can find the truth and hope of Jesus.

12:15.054 --> 12:16.476
It's a sacrificial thing.

12:17.137 --> 12:23.666
If I could put it in one quick sentence, Jesus' purpose is greater than my preferences.

12:24.610 --> 12:27.975
Jesus' purpose is greater than my preferences.

12:29.597 --> 12:50.226
In fact, you could look at the four things we've talked about, the personality of Jesus, the posture of Jesus, the purpose of Jesus, the power of Jesus, that all of these things in our lives should be greater than our own personal preferences, that we

12:50.466 --> 13:05.448
should be making space for those who need to know Jesus, that we should be serving with humility, that we should be sacrificing for those who need to know Jesus, that we should be leaning into the power of the Holy Spirit, that people's lives might be changed over what we prefer.

13:07.251 --> 13:08.874
Because we have preferences, don't we?

13:08.894 --> 13:11.177
I mean, I have preferences.

13:12.219 --> 13:19.890
You know, I come here on a Sunday morning, and if you a call connects us home, one of the things you heard this morning, you know we hear every single Sunday.

13:20.290 --> 13:24.396
Every single Sunday we say, hey, if you're new here, right?

13:24.436 --> 13:25.638
We would love to meet you.

13:26.019 --> 13:27.881
Here's a card scanned to cue our code.

13:28.082 --> 13:29.243
We'll leave you in the lobby.

13:29.344 --> 13:34.411
And there are some of you I know who have said, man, every single Sunday.

13:36.034 --> 13:37.015
Well, you think it's bad for you?

13:37.035 --> 13:38.758
I'm in three services every Sunday.

13:42.363 --> 13:45.668
But why am I setting aside that small preference?

13:46.529 --> 13:49.714
Because I know that there are people even here today who are here for the first time.

13:50.274 --> 13:54.359
who need to connect with someone, who need community, that want to get to know someone.

13:54.759 --> 13:59.025
So when you go, well, that's not really what I prefer, yeah, because it's not about you.

14:01.788 --> 14:16.466
And you might say, oh, you know what, Jeff, like when it comes like inviting a neighbor or inviting a friend or reaching out to someone and saying, hey, talking about my faith, inviting the church, that's not my preference.

14:17.506 --> 14:21.190
Yeah, because the mission of the local church, if you're part of this church, it's not about you.

14:22.251 --> 14:27.776
But that's our purpose, is to set aside our preferences for that purpose.

14:30.479 --> 14:37.746
If you're here on a Sunday morning and you go, oh man, Jeff, you know, I know the room's full about 1158.

14:37.966 --> 14:42.891
That seems, I prefer my service time.

14:43.852 --> 14:45.714
I didn't even get here early to get my seat.

14:49.154 --> 14:50.235
Preference or purpose?

14:51.376 --> 14:53.678
It's choosing preference over purpose.

14:53.778 --> 14:54.559
We do this.

14:56.281 --> 15:09.914
But when, when you choose to put the personality, the posture, the purpose, the power that Jesus calls us to as a local church over your preferences, incredible things happen.

15:10.034 --> 15:14.478
And what I want to do is I want to show you what this looked like in the early church.

15:14.518 --> 15:16.720
Because the early church got this right.

15:16.940 --> 15:18.962
If you want to do something fun,

15:19.074 --> 15:25.884
I recognize this is pastor fun, but if you want to do something fun, when this series is over, read the book of Acts.

15:26.345 --> 15:29.029
It's basically a group of people trying to figure this out.

15:29.550 --> 15:34.618
They look at who Jesus is and they go, man, okay, we got to figure out what this church thing looks like.

15:34.658 --> 15:37.062
We took the baton, now what does it look like?

15:37.362 --> 15:40.687
So let me show you what it looked like when they got it right, okay?

15:41.568 --> 15:47.858
This is how it starts is all the believers devoted themselves to the apostles' teaching and to fellowship

15:48.002 --> 15:52.367
and to sharing in meals, including the Lord's Supper and to prayer.

15:53.748 --> 15:54.689
And you go, wow.

15:55.810 --> 15:59.655
Doesn't that, you read that and you go, that sounds so, you know, like warm.

16:00.255 --> 16:01.256
They're all hanging out.

16:01.617 --> 16:04.260
They probably had like a chakudiri board down the middle.

16:04.300 --> 16:09.725
You know, the right music, great drinks, probably was a great time.

16:10.026 --> 16:10.827
Do you want to know something?

16:11.127 --> 16:12.368
It was nothing like that.

16:14.090 --> 16:17.714
You had a group of people who prior to finding Jesus,

16:18.210 --> 16:19.953
Many would never have hung out together.

16:21.575 --> 16:23.438
You know who is at this table?

16:24.800 --> 16:29.306
That person who is so needy, like they never stop talking to you.

16:29.907 --> 16:31.169
Like you never get a word in.

16:31.229 --> 16:33.633
That's who's at that dinner.

16:35.035 --> 16:36.136
If you're there, they're with you.

16:38.840 --> 16:41.985
That person who you go, man, I'm jealous of them.

16:42.025 --> 16:43.046
They make so much money.

16:43.087 --> 16:43.968
I make so much less.

16:44.128 --> 16:45.490
You're both at the table together.

16:46.338 --> 16:50.205
These are people who are from different economic backgrounds, different ethnic backgrounds.

16:50.245 --> 16:59.884
I mean, this was a pirate ship of a table together because of what Jesus had done for them.

17:00.826 --> 17:09.362
And they devoted themselves to teaching each other what it meant to apprentice to Jesus.

17:10.274 --> 17:12.898
It says, a deep sense of awe came over them all.

17:13.138 --> 17:16.082
And the apostles performed many miraculous signs and wonders.

17:16.422 --> 17:20.428
And all the believers met together in one place, and they shared everything they had.

17:20.468 --> 17:21.269
What do you see here?

17:21.289 --> 17:23.752
The posture of Jesus, as they share everything they have.

17:24.073 --> 17:26.716
The power of Jesus is the Holy Spirit is working through them.

17:26.977 --> 17:35.348
It says, they sold their property, and they sold their possessions, and they shared their money with those in need, completely giving up their preferences.

17:37.551 --> 17:39.634
They worshiped together at the temple each day,

17:39.810 --> 17:43.874
They're at the temple where everybody else is talking about, hey, this Messiah that you're waiting for.

17:43.914 --> 17:45.235
Yeah, we met them already.

17:47.338 --> 17:47.978
It's Jesus.

17:49.179 --> 17:50.721
They met in homes for the Lord's Supper.

17:50.761 --> 17:57.207
They shared their meals with great joy and generosity, all well praising God and enjoying the goodwill of all the people.

17:57.548 --> 18:03.774
And each day the Lord added to their fellowship, those who were being saved.

18:03.794 --> 18:06.797
They are seeking and saving the lost.

18:07.398 --> 18:07.698
How?

18:09.954 --> 18:12.557
They put the personality of Jesus.

18:13.639 --> 18:14.901
They put the posture of Jesus.

18:16.863 --> 18:22.831
They put the purpose of Jesus and the power of Jesus over their own preferences every single day.

18:23.172 --> 18:29.921
Because when you put purpose over preferences, people's lives are changed by Jesus.

18:32.384 --> 18:35.989
It's not easy, but it's not complicated to understand.

18:38.292 --> 18:39.954
And you know what?

18:40.034 --> 18:42.558
You read that and you go, wow, man, they were killing it.

18:43.379 --> 18:45.082
We'll just go over a few more chapters.

18:47.225 --> 18:52.032
And what you end up finding out is they end up struggling with this.

18:52.933 --> 18:53.494
You know why?

18:53.855 --> 18:54.896
Because they drift.

18:55.477 --> 18:58.301
They drift towards becoming more insider focus.

18:58.702 --> 18:59.944
And I'll give you an example.

18:59.964 --> 19:01.686
You flip over to Acts 15.

19:02.768 --> 19:09.458
And what happens is they struggle to give up their insider preferences because

19:09.634 --> 19:12.657
A different group joins them, the Gentiles.

19:13.818 --> 19:16.141
See, these were Jewish people who had found Jesus.

19:17.142 --> 19:19.924
And now there are Gentiles finding Jesus.

19:20.685 --> 19:30.535
And they don't, they don't want to hang out with Gentiles and they want the Gentiles to follow all of their rules, all of their preferences, all of their Jewish traditions.

19:31.015 --> 19:33.078
And one of those traditions is circumcision.

19:33.838 --> 19:37.522
And they're saying, Hey, these Gentiles, they got to follow our Jewish traditions.

19:37.794 --> 19:39.936
I'm not sure I want to lay down those preferences.

19:40.317 --> 19:42.519
I'm not sure I want to set those things to the side.

19:44.201 --> 19:45.222
And they got to figure this out.

19:46.142 --> 19:48.285
So they do what churches do and they need to figure things out.

19:48.305 --> 19:49.726
They put a committee together.

19:49.746 --> 19:50.387
They have a meeting.

19:51.868 --> 19:53.150
It's like the first church meeting.

19:54.591 --> 19:57.934
If you've ever been in a church meeting, I promise you it was more exciting than that.

19:59.176 --> 19:59.636
This is it.

19:59.716 --> 20:05.362
So the apostles and the elders met together to resolve this issue.

20:06.306 --> 20:12.073
And at the meeting, after a long discussion, Peter stood and addressed him as follows.

20:12.975 --> 20:22.467
He said, brothers, you all know that God chose me from among you some time ago to preach to the Gentiles so they could hear the good news and believe.

20:22.527 --> 20:23.348
What's Peter saying here?

20:23.368 --> 20:31.198
He's saying, guys, guys, listen, you all know that I was called to preach to the Gentiles.

20:32.840 --> 20:34.482
What did you think was going to happen?

20:35.138 --> 20:36.920
How bad a preacher do you think I am?

20:37.942 --> 20:38.983
They're coming to Jesus.

20:39.103 --> 20:40.625
That was the whole point, guys.

20:42.208 --> 20:43.790
He says, God knows people's hearts.

20:45.792 --> 20:51.120
And he confirmed that he accepts Gentiles because he's giving them the Holy Spirit.

20:51.140 --> 20:52.822
We see the power of God in their lives.

20:53.082 --> 20:59.871
Just as he did to us, he made no distinction between us and them, for he cleansed their hearts through faith.

21:01.113 --> 21:04.818
Not through all these traditions and rules that you have, through faith.

21:05.282 --> 21:15.495
So why are you now challenging God by burdening the Gentile believers with a yoke that neither we nor our ancestors were able to bear?

21:16.216 --> 21:22.004
We believe that we are all saved the same way by the undeserved grace of the Lord Jesus Christ.

21:22.104 --> 21:23.646
We're all saved by Christ.

21:23.966 --> 21:26.089
We're not saved by these traditions guys that you have.

21:26.349 --> 21:30.815
Stop putting all the traditions on the Gentiles that are not even a part of this.

21:30.835 --> 21:33.298
And so my judgment, so what happens is

21:33.442 --> 21:35.364
James, the brother of Jesus, stands up.

21:35.404 --> 21:37.386
He gives a speech later on that you should read.

21:37.406 --> 21:38.327
You don't have time for it today.

21:38.628 --> 21:46.356
And he says this in verse 19, and so my judgment is that we should not make it difficult for the Gentiles who are turning to God.

21:47.757 --> 21:56.687
He says, listen, there are a few things we're going to set aside, but outside of that, let's not get in the way of these Gentiles who are coming to find Jesus.

21:56.707 --> 21:59.570
He's saying, we should not make it difficult

21:59.906 --> 22:06.115
For those who are turning to Christ, if people are trying to find Jesus, let's not make it so difficult.

22:07.137 --> 22:17.872
Now, for some of you, if you're a church person and you hear that, the thing you're wondering is, sounds like just talking about watering down the gospel, water down the Bible.

22:17.933 --> 22:21.398
That's not what James is saying, definitely not.

22:21.618 --> 22:22.639
And that's not what I'm saying.

22:24.102 --> 22:29.810
Listen, the truth of the gospel, the truth of the gospel is gonna be offensive.

22:30.402 --> 22:32.024
There's a part of the gospel that offends.

22:32.144 --> 22:33.625
It calls us out on our stuff.

22:34.746 --> 22:36.328
Following Jesus is a hard thing.

22:37.169 --> 22:38.270
It's gonna be offensive.

22:39.190 --> 22:41.753
But that doesn't mean that we should be offensive.

22:42.934 --> 22:47.619
That we wanna not be in the way and get between people and Jesus.

22:47.659 --> 22:51.422
We wanna do everything we can to make a way for people to find Jesus.

22:51.582 --> 22:59.410
I was listening to a guy this week who came to Christ at our location in Aurelia this past year and we baptized him.

22:59.714 --> 23:02.677
And we were asking him about his very first experience coming to church.

23:04.119 --> 23:07.423
He said, well, I came, came on my own, came on my pickup truck.

23:08.104 --> 23:10.386
I didn't know what to expect, like zero idea.

23:11.307 --> 23:16.133
He says, I drove down the street and I thought it would be like 20 people inside.

23:16.173 --> 23:19.957
He says, I saw the building and I was so nervous.

23:20.698 --> 23:27.826
And I drove in and there was a guy in the parking lot with Mickey Mouse hands on his hands.

23:28.418 --> 23:30.742
And he was pointing me where to park my car.

23:33.626 --> 23:36.591
And he said, so I mean, he was smiling.

23:36.711 --> 23:37.512
He seemed friendly.

23:37.693 --> 23:39.375
And I mean Mickey Mouse hands.

23:39.415 --> 23:41.238
They're the universal sign of peace, right?

23:41.258 --> 23:44.403
It's like, who's going to hurt you with Mickey Mouse hands on?

23:45.865 --> 23:47.548
And so he says, I went in the parking lot.

23:48.710 --> 23:51.594
And they put me in a spot.

23:51.614 --> 23:52.636
And I drove in that spot.

23:53.197 --> 23:56.562
And I sat there trying to get enough nerve to go inside the building.

23:57.634 --> 24:00.717
And I watched the time ticking on my clock, on my watch.

24:02.379 --> 24:04.821
And I was sort of like, am I gonna go in?

24:05.021 --> 24:05.882
Am I not gonna go in?

24:05.902 --> 24:06.643
Am I gonna go in?

24:06.703 --> 24:07.584
Am I not gonna go in?

24:08.325 --> 24:11.128
And he said, there was like one to two minutes left.

24:11.268 --> 24:13.610
And I said, okay, like it's now or never.

24:13.830 --> 24:16.973
And I got on my truck and I closed the door and I walked in the building.

24:17.614 --> 24:19.015
And he said, there weren't 20 people there.

24:19.056 --> 24:20.117
It was like a lot of people there.

24:22.539 --> 24:25.522
And in that moment, he began a journey to Jesus.

24:27.426 --> 24:31.450
Now, do we need people in the parking lot for me?

24:32.631 --> 24:33.813
No.

24:33.833 --> 24:34.954
I know where to park my car.

24:36.716 --> 24:38.237
Truthfully, it's a big parking lot.

24:38.257 --> 24:39.338
We could all park our own cars.

24:40.560 --> 24:41.020
So why?

24:41.941 --> 24:45.264
Why would we have people out there in the parking lot?

24:45.284 --> 24:49.188
Because we don't want people to come in and go, man, there's nobody here to greet me.

24:49.789 --> 24:51.210
This isn't a one place at all.

24:51.791 --> 24:53.293
I don't even know kind of where to go.

24:53.313 --> 24:54.674
How does this all work?

24:54.786 --> 24:57.730
All of those things are barriers between people and Jesus.

24:58.931 --> 25:01.014
And we need to remove those barriers.

25:04.177 --> 25:05.679
It's the same thing when it comes to music.

25:06.200 --> 25:08.102
You might come here and say, I love the music.

25:08.122 --> 25:11.366
I love it, but you know what?

25:11.827 --> 25:14.330
I just wish, the music just went longer.

25:14.390 --> 25:16.252
I wish we sang eight more songs.

25:16.652 --> 25:17.674
That would be amazing.

25:18.755 --> 25:24.562
Well, maybe it would be for you, but if I've got my friend or you've got your friend and they've never been in church before,

25:24.738 --> 25:27.201
That's 40 minutes of songs they've never heard before.

25:28.182 --> 25:29.684
Like are these real songs?

25:30.425 --> 25:33.007
Like I was at karaoke Friday night, they didn't have these songs.

25:33.448 --> 25:35.570
Like the lyrics are here, but I don't know any of the songs.

25:37.312 --> 25:39.575
Like I don't get it.

25:39.595 --> 25:40.396
I don't understand.

25:40.436 --> 25:42.679
I don't understand how this works.

25:42.699 --> 25:46.543
We don't want that to be a barrier between people and Jesus.

25:47.764 --> 25:52.690
We wanna remove as many barriers as possible between people and Jesus.

25:54.626 --> 26:05.843
See, when we talk about a church that our community needs, our community needs a church that puts the personality of Jesus over our preferences.

26:06.784 --> 26:11.772
Our community needs a church that puts the posture of Jesus over our preferences.

26:12.192 --> 26:16.278
Our community needs a church that puts the purpose of Jesus over our preferences.

26:16.759 --> 26:21.386
Our community needs a church that puts the power of Jesus over our preferences.

26:22.327 --> 26:24.210
And when you look at the early church,

26:24.578 --> 26:30.445
They were so committed to this so that people would know the good news of Jesus that they died for it.

26:31.085 --> 26:31.786
They died for it.

26:32.967 --> 26:34.890
They died telling people about Jesus.

26:34.950 --> 26:39.294
They died being out finding people and gathering them and telling them about Jesus.

26:39.315 --> 26:42.598
They died because they got around tables and told people around Jesus.

26:42.618 --> 26:45.582
They died doing it, preaching the good news.

26:48.245 --> 26:49.586
But we all have preferences.

26:51.650 --> 26:52.471
We all have preferences.

26:52.511 --> 26:56.555
Where are your preferences of barrier for others to find Jesus?

26:58.417 --> 27:08.609
It could be Sunday morning preferences, preference about where you sit, preference about what music, preference about, you know, we should run this program or we should be running that program or we should run this because I want that and I had this.

27:10.411 --> 27:12.493
Well, I, you know, I'm not sure this is exactly how I do it.

27:12.513 --> 27:14.255
We all have preferences.

27:14.755 --> 27:15.737
What are your preferences?

27:17.138 --> 27:18.099
Well, you know what?

27:18.119 --> 27:18.560
I don't know.

27:19.260 --> 27:20.722
Like getting into my neighbor,

27:21.730 --> 27:23.092
and inviting them?

27:24.254 --> 27:26.177
I don't know about that.

27:26.337 --> 27:27.859
That's uncomfortable.

27:28.681 --> 27:28.941
Yes.

27:31.545 --> 27:31.765
Yes.

27:33.588 --> 27:36.793
The mission of the local church is just like following Jesus.

27:38.796 --> 27:39.297
Challenging.

27:40.999 --> 27:50.514
But if we're willing to step out, I have a friend who this week went around, said, I realize I don't know my neighbors very well, went around,

27:50.594 --> 27:57.905
invited all his neighbors and had a barbecue in the backyard and said, man, who knows what God's going to do?

28:00.469 --> 28:01.570
Who knows what God's going to do?

28:02.111 --> 28:03.493
Now, you could say, well, that sounds hard.

28:04.715 --> 28:07.740
I'd rather just eat chips and watch Netflix like that's much simpler.

28:09.342 --> 28:13.168
Well, I know the potential of what God's going to do with chips and Netflix if I do that.

28:14.950 --> 28:20.178
And I know the potential of when I reach out to someone who doesn't know the hope of Jesus and what God's going to do through that.

28:24.034 --> 28:30.001
17, almost 18 years ago, we were living in Oakville.

28:31.683 --> 28:34.186
And this church had just begun, just started.

28:35.227 --> 28:36.589
Maybe six months to a year old.

28:38.531 --> 28:41.034
And I had come up for an interview.

28:41.114 --> 28:43.897
I was at another church for seven years and I came for an interview.

28:46.020 --> 28:48.983
And we got to the point where the interviews were over.

28:49.143 --> 28:51.506
I'd been offered the job and we had to make a decision.

28:53.090 --> 28:55.975
And I'll never forget, I'll never forget where I was standing.

28:57.257 --> 29:08.494
Leslie and I were standing in our townhouse, two little boys, one brand new, and I said, well, what are we gonna do?

29:09.636 --> 29:10.317
Like this is it.

29:11.519 --> 29:12.360
Gotta make a decision.

29:14.283 --> 29:16.146
And she said to me, what do you wanna do?

29:19.251 --> 29:21.074
And here's what I had observed.

29:24.002 --> 29:27.527
The people who began this church, there were five people on staff.

29:28.588 --> 29:29.890
They left their jobs.

29:30.491 --> 29:31.532
They left careers.

29:32.093 --> 29:33.254
They'd taken pay cuts.

29:35.277 --> 29:50.237
And I watched on a Sunday morning, people were getting in pickup trucks at four in the morning, pulling like four 22-foot trailers to church on a Sunday, setting up tearing down in two movie theaters, four in the morning, giving financially all they could.

29:50.257 --> 29:53.842
I mean,

29:55.106 --> 29:57.228
Honestly, we're a bit soft compared to those people.

30:01.313 --> 30:11.003
And I said to Leslie, these people have given up everything to reach people.

30:11.023 --> 30:14.487
They have given up everything to seek and save the lost.

30:17.450 --> 30:21.234
And I don't know when I'll ever get a chance to work with a group of people like this again.

30:24.354 --> 30:27.239
And you might think, oh man, the church must have really been booming.

30:27.800 --> 30:31.306
The church was 50% of the size of the day it opened.

30:32.648 --> 30:38.958
Because half the people realized how uncomfortable it is to attend church in a movie theater.

30:39.760 --> 30:46.711
With sticky floors and set up tear down and starting at five in the morning and pushing through snow storms, and they moved on.

30:48.675 --> 30:50.738
Because it was too uncomfortable for them.

30:54.306 --> 30:56.890
The local church is called to sacrifice.

30:59.514 --> 31:03.881
I know that's hard, but you told me earlier, you didn't want me to water it down.

31:06.224 --> 31:06.685
It's hard.

31:09.029 --> 31:12.194
It's a sacrifice to point people to Jesus.

31:13.355 --> 31:18.343
But when we're all in on being the church, our community needs, it's worth it.

31:19.365 --> 31:20.927
It's worth giving our lives to.

31:21.728 --> 31:22.770
I've been doing this.

31:23.010 --> 31:27.497
for over 17 years, I've given my whole life to this, to see people.

31:27.577 --> 31:35.730
And I can't tell you the hundreds and hundreds of people who've been baptized, marriages that have been rescued, people who've been changed and transformed.

31:38.034 --> 31:40.237
And I don't regret one second of it.

31:40.818 --> 31:43.021
And I have some crappy days sometimes.

31:44.444 --> 31:48.530
I do not regret for one second giving my life to the local church.

31:48.770 --> 31:57.683
I do not regret for one second being a church that wants to reach their community, and I would do it all over again, and I wouldn't have to even think about it.

31:59.065 --> 31:59.305
Why?

32:00.707 --> 32:02.870
Because of people's lives who have been changed.

32:07.457 --> 32:12.384
Frankly, I mean, we've got lots of people coming to connect with us right now, which is amazing.

32:14.387 --> 32:16.370
And if you're somebody who's here and you're

32:16.450 --> 32:20.234
You're searching and you're seeking and you're trying to find Jesus, I'm so glad you're here.

32:21.595 --> 32:29.883
And if you're here and you're alongside someone, you're walking with someone who's seeking and you're walking alongside them, and I'm so glad that you're doing that.

32:29.903 --> 32:31.104
That's what our church is all about.

32:32.506 --> 32:38.351
And if you're here and you're like, man, I'm serving, you're on mission with us, you've joined us on mission, I'm so glad you're here.

32:38.391 --> 32:45.138
And if you're here and you would say, hey, I'm actually sick, I'm going through something really difficult and I'm here to heal, I'm so glad you're here.

32:45.218 --> 32:49.264
But if you are not in any of those categories, frankly, we're running out of room for you.

32:52.149 --> 32:54.052
And we have people waiting in the lobby last week.

32:56.095 --> 33:04.088
And we need to be the church our community needs and give our lives to the mission of seeing people know Jesus.

33:05.410 --> 33:10.578
And that means submitting our preferences to the cross of Christ.

33:12.002 --> 33:16.606
So where is your desire to make the movement of the church comfortable for you?

33:17.687 --> 33:18.969
And how can you uproot that?

33:19.850 --> 33:25.835
And where are you getting in the way and not jumping on mission, the movement of the local church to see others reached?

33:26.236 --> 33:31.961
And if you can't be a part of the movement here, then find a church that you can be a part of and see lives change and transformed.

33:32.482 --> 33:41.170
And this week, I would encourage you, what's one way you can give up your preferences to join the movement of the local church in sharing the hope

33:41.506 --> 33:46.712
of Jesus to find your place to seeing lives changed.

33:48.675 --> 33:56.224
Now, if you're here today and you would say, listen, Jeff, you're really passionate about people knowing the gospel and the good news of Jesus.

33:57.466 --> 33:58.667
I don't know what that is.

33:59.929 --> 34:00.870
I've never heard that.

34:01.711 --> 34:03.934
You seem to be passionate about something I don't understand.

34:04.915 --> 34:07.879
And if that's you, I just want to share with you what the good news is.

34:09.240 --> 34:10.482
And here is the good news.

34:11.266 --> 34:13.629
You see the sin and the brokenness in our world.

34:14.269 --> 34:15.731
You see the shame in our world.

34:17.132 --> 34:20.656
And the truth is you see that same shame and brokenness in you.

34:22.398 --> 34:32.489
And scripture is very clear that actually the sin and brokenness in our world, it's worse than you realize because it's what separates you from God.

34:34.051 --> 34:40.498
He is holy and he can't be with sin and that separation is worse than you might imagine.

34:42.562 --> 34:43.543
But here's the good news.

34:44.445 --> 34:48.090
The good news is God's love is bigger than you've ever realized.

34:48.110 --> 34:51.035
It's bigger than you could ever imagine in your whole life.

34:51.455 --> 34:54.139
His love for you is greater than in a lifetime.

34:54.179 --> 35:11.826
You could ever even come close to getting your head around to the point that he would send his son to live a perfect life and die on the cross for your sin, that you might find forgiveness, that you might find healing, that you might be made whole, that you might know God and that you could have a relationship with him, not just today,

35:12.290 --> 35:13.371
but into eternity.

35:14.873 --> 35:18.677
Because if you don't have a relationship with Him today, that also continues into eternity.

35:19.498 --> 35:26.826
And we desperately want you to know the hope of Jesus, the love of God, and how He wants to change and transform you.

35:27.226 --> 35:30.590
And I'm gonna close in prayer today if you're like, man, that does sound like good news, Jeff.

35:31.871 --> 35:33.353
I do want that in my life.

35:34.494 --> 35:37.758
Then what I'm gonna do is give you a chance to pray with me and respond to that today.

35:37.798 --> 35:39.900
And you can come and hang out with me after if you've got questions.

35:40.220 --> 35:41.842
We'd love to get a Bible in your hand.

35:43.490 --> 35:48.336
Because this news is so good, we don't want to keep it with a secret.

35:49.117 --> 35:51.660
We want to share it with as many people as possible.

35:52.301 --> 35:58.328
Because what our community needs, more than anything else, is the hope of Jesus.

35:59.350 --> 36:02.914
And to know how he loves them and wants to change and transform their lives.

36:03.955 --> 36:04.636
Let's pray together.

36:04.696 --> 36:06.098
God, we come to you today.

36:08.866 --> 36:14.234
And for those of you who are saying, man, I want that, Jeff, that good news, I want that in my life.

36:15.535 --> 36:21.223
You can pray with me, God, I come to you, recognizing your love for me.

36:24.348 --> 36:28.454
And I bring my sin to you and my shame and ask that you would forgive me and heal me.

36:31.158 --> 36:34.322
And God, I pray that as I turn

36:35.106 --> 36:42.173
and choose a different path, a path of following you, a path of surrendering my life to you, a path of knowing you in my life that you would meet me there.

36:43.934 --> 36:54.124
Thank you for your death, for your resurrection, for forgiveness and healing, and a relationship with you today and into eternity.

36:54.144 --> 36:55.605
And God, we pray as a church.

36:57.227 --> 37:04.914
We pray as a church that we could never be accused of knowing

37:05.154 --> 37:13.721
the hope of Jesus and keeping it a secret, but that we would shout it with our lives every single day.

37:15.487 --> 37:16.530
And we pray this in your name.

